article.headline: Montana 90, Portland State 62
article.story:
PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) -- Former Portland prep star Julie Deming
scored a career-high 25 points to lead Montana in a 90-62 victory
over Portland State.

Senior point guard Brooklynn Lorenzen tied Montana's single-game
record with 15 assists and had 11 points.

Reserve forward Jody McLeod finished with 12 points as Montana
(6-0, 17-4) rattled off its seventh straight victory.

Junior center Hollie Tyler and forward Juliann Keller also
contributed double-figure scoring to the Lady Griz's highest point
total in two seasons.

Lorenzen, who didn't commit a turnover while playing 29 minutes,
tied the mark of former Lady Griz standout Kelly Pilcher, who twice
tallied 15 assists in 1994.

Sarah Hedgepeth's 18 points led Portland State (0-6, 3-17).
